data.name: FilePattern.ToolTip
data.value:
This field controls how URLs are generated.
Available Variables: {A-Z} Character Range These will be based off of ASCII character codes, so {A-z} or {a-Z} may have unintended side effects. {0-99} Unpadded Number Range It will generate based on the range provided. {0-99} produce every number from 0 to 99, without padding. {p0-99} Padded Number Range It will generate based on the range provided. {p0-99} produce every number, padded with zeros, from 00 to 99. Padding is based off of end number. For example, if the end number is 1000, it will pad single digit numbers with 3 zeros like this: 0003. {jpg|dat} Word lists Words separated by the | character
